headline: Stock futures, October PCE, HP and Dell earnings: 3 Things
summary: US stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) are mixed Wednesday morning as the Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) and S&P 500 (^GSPC) climbed to record highs in yesterday's session. Treasury yields (^TYX, ^TNX, ^FVX) dip further ahead of October's Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) index due out later this morning. Dell Technologies (DELL) and HP Inc. (HPQ) slide even lower in this morning's pre-market trading after their respective earnings results indicated a slowdown in the PC market. Catch Yahoo Finance executive editor Brian Sozzi's full interview with HP CEO Enrique Lores. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: HP, Dell's weak forecasts spark share selloff, doubts over PC market recovery
summary: Dell fell 13% in trading before the bell, with the company set to shed nearly $13 billion from its $99.50 billion market value, after it forecast quarterly revenue below estimates.  HP dropped 9% and its market capitalisation was set to shrink by more than $3 billion, from $37.68 billion on Tuesday, following a quarterly profit projection that was short of the market view.  Traditional PC demand has weakened after a post-pandemic boom, while AI-powered computers have yet to see mass adoption despite some interest from corporate and education sectors.
